  <brief_title>Comparison Between Laparoscopic Common Bile Duct Exploration and Intraoperative ERCP for Management of Common Bile Duct Stones</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Mansoura University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Mansoura University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Many options are available for management of common bile duct stones. the most recent
      development in this field is single-session approach by one of two methods; laparoscopic
      common bile duct exploration and intraoperative endoscopic sphincterotomy. In this study, the
      investigators prospectively compare these two methods for management of patients with
      preoperatively diagnosed common bile duct stones to settle the best option.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
